# AI-301: Artificial Intelligence  
**Trimester:** Fall 2024  
**Credits:** 4  
**Level:** Upper Division Undergraduate  
**Prerequisites:** Python Programming, Linear Algebra, Probability, Data Structures  

---

# Course Description

AI-301 provides a comprehensive introduction to Artificial Intelligence, integrating theoretical foundations with hands-on tool building.  

Students will master:

- Search algorithms  
- Machine Learning  
- Deep Learning  
- Reinforcement Learning  
- AI Deployment & MLOps  
- Ethical AI & Bias Auditing  

The curriculum mirrors top-tier courses such as MIT 6.036, Stanford CS221/CS229, and Harvard CS50 AI, emphasizing project-based learning where students build deployable AI systems.

---

# Learning Outcomes

Upon successful completion, students will be able to:

1. Design and implement AI algorithms (Search, ML, DL, RL)  
2. Build end-to-end AI tools (image classifiers, chatbots, predictors)  
3. Deploy AI systems as scalable web services  
4. Audit AI systems for bias and ethical risk  
5. Communicate AI concepts through technical documentation and presentations  

---

