# Grading Policy

| Component | Weight |
|------------|--------|
| Weekly Labs (7) | 25% |
| Midterm Project | 15% |
| Capstone Project | 30% |
| Midterm Exam | 15% |
| Final Exam | 15% |

---

# Weekly Schedule

## Week 1: AI Foundations & Problem Solving
- Intelligent agents and PEAS framework  
- BFS, DFS, A* search  
- Ethics: Bias in routing systems  

**Lab 1:** Implement BFS, DFS, A* (Grid World)

---

## Week 2: Machine Learning Fundamentals
- Supervised vs. Unsupervised Learning  
- Decision Trees, Naive Bayes  
- Evaluation metrics  

**Lab 2:** Build a Naive Bayes Spam Classifier

---

## Week 3: Deep Learning
- Perceptrons & Backpropagation  
- CNNs & Transfer Learning  
- Ethics: Deepfakes  

**Lab 3:** Train CNN on CIFAR-10

---

## Week 4: Reinforcement Learning
- MDPs  
- Q-Learning  
- Deep Q Networks  

**Lab 4:** Solve FrozenLake / CartPole

---

## Week 5: AI Tool Engineering & Deployment
- MLOps lifecycle  
- Flask APIs  
- Docker containerization  
- Cloud deployment  

**Lab 5:** Deploy ML model as Flask API + Docker

---

## Week 6: Ethics & Future of AI
- Bias sources and fairness metrics  
- Explainable AI (SHAP, LIME)  
- AGI Safety & Alignment  

**Lab 6:** Bias Audit using AIF360

---

## Week 7: Midterm Exam
- Theory + Coding  

---

## Weeks 8–13: Capstone Project

| Week | Focus | Deliverable |
|------|-------|------------|
| 8 | Proposal | 1-page proposal |
| 9 | Data | Clean dataset |
| 10 | Model | Working prototype |
| 11 | Deployment | API deployed |
| 12 | Ethics | Bias audit report |
| 13 | Polish | Demo + slides |

---

## Week 14: Final Exam + Capstone Demos

- Final comprehensive exam  
- 3-minute pitch + live demo  

---

# Capstone Project

Students build a full AI tool including:

- Data acquisition  
- Model training  
- Deployment  
- Bias audit  
- Technical documentation  

### Example Project Options

- Medical Diagnosis Assistant  
- Game-Playing AI  
- Financial Prediction Tool  
- NLP Chatbot  

